{"art": [], "author": [{"email_address": "wgstexas@gmail.com", "first_name": "W. Gardner", "id": 122, "last_name": "Selby", "name_slug": "w-gardner-selby", "on_staff_page": 84, "phone": "", "photo": null, "publication": {"id": 3, "publication_name": "Austin American-Statesman", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/3/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/122/", "title": "Former PolitiFact Texas editor", "twitter": ""}], "canonical_url": "/texas/statements/2010/jun/20/donna-campbell/gop-nominee-says-lloyd-doggett-austin-no-1-liberal/", "edition": {"adkey": "Editions", "advalue": "Texas", "edition": "Texas", "edition_slug": "texas", "has_afterthefact": false, "id": 2, "index_page": false, "meter_name": "The Texas Truth-O-Meter", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/edition/2/"}, "editor": [], "facebook_headline": null, "id": 1915, "in_future": false, "is_pundit": false, "make_public": true, "preview": true, "researcher": [{"email_address": "wgstexas@gmail.com", "first_name": "W. Gardner", "id": 122, "last_name": "Selby", "name_slug": "w-gardner-selby", "on_staff_page": 84, "phone": "", "photo": null, "publication": {"id": 3, "publication_name": "Austin American-Statesman", "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/publication/3/"}, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/staffer/122/", "title": "Former PolitiFact Texas editor", "twitter": ""}], "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statement/1915/", "ruling": {"adkey": "Truth-O-Meter", "advalue": "False", "id": 5, "resource_uri": "/api/v/2/statementruling/5/", "ruling": "False", "ruling_graphic": "https://s3.amazonaws.com/static.politifact.com/rulings/tom-false.png", "ruling_slug": "false"}, "ruling_comments": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Rousing delegates to the Republican Party of  Texas&rsquo;s state convention, physician Donna Campbell of Columbus lit into  her November foe, calling U.S. Rep. Lloyd Doggett, D-Austin, &ldquo;the most  liberal man in the United States Congress.&rdquo;</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Campbell&rsquo;s  characterization June 12 touched off a supportive outburst from the  partisans gathered in Dallas.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">No doubt,  Doggett, elected to the House  in 1994 after stints as a state senator  and Texas Supreme Court  justice, has long been a liberal&mdash;proudly so. We  wondered, though, if  he&rsquo;s among the nation&rsquo;s most liberal members  compared, say, to solons  from other left-leaning districts.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">When we reached Campbell to seek the basis for her statement, she&nbsp; couldn&rsquo;t immediately visit; she was on duty in a hospital.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Next, we endeavored to gauge Doggett's liberal lean following a methodology forged by PolitiFact in Washington when it </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"> explored a  similar charge. &nbsp;In June 2008, the  expected GOP presidential nominee,  Arizona Sen. John McCain, said</span><a href=\"http://www.politifact.com/truth-o-meter/statements/2008/jun/16/john-mccain/obama-not-no-1-in-other-ratings/\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000099; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: underline;\">then-Sen.  Barack Obama had accumulated the Senate&rsquo;s most  liberal voting record</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">. PolitiFact found that Barely True.<br /></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Also, we presumed that despite her wording, Campbell was comparing Doggett to  all his colleagues, male and female, in the House and Senate. But for our  analysis, we limited ourselves to the 435-member House; that seemed both  reasonable and more doable than trying to compare Doggett's record to every other member of the House and Senate.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">We started our check by clicking  to online ratings compiled by the National Journal, a nonpartisan  political magazine. According to the Journal, Doggett&rsquo;s 2009 voting  record made him the</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"> </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">House&rsquo;s 163rd most liberal member, more  so on social issues than economic or foreign policy, according to its  tabulation of 92 House votes. From Texas alone, seven other Democrats  had more liberal records, the Journal said.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">We also looked  at the two preceding years. According to the Journal, Doggett&rsquo;s votes  in 2007 and 2008 made him the House&rsquo;s 119th most liberal member and 97th  most liberal member, respectively, in those years&mdash;not No. 1.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Congressional  Quarterly doesn&rsquo;t rate members on a conservative-liberal teeter-totter.  Instead it gauges whether members vote in step with the president or  their party. In 2009, CQ says, Doggett voted with President Obama 89  percent of the time and with his party 95 percent of the time.</span><br /><br /><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">According to  an online chart, Doggett&rsquo;s votes land landed him among members most  likely to support their party and president</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">, </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">which does not  put him in centrist company. Still, about 200 members, all Democrats,  voted more often than Doggett in accord with Obama and about 175 members  were more likely to vote the Democratic Party&rsquo;s way, CQ charts suggest.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">For another  comparison, we turned to voteview.com, a site overseen by Keith Poole, a  political scientist at the University of Georgia. According to  voteview&rsquo;s latest review of the House, Doggett is about the 117th most  liberal member. Poole told us in an e-mail there is &ldquo;no denying that  Doggett is a conventional liberal but he is not an &lsquo;extreme&rsquo; liberal.&rdquo; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">After we  alerted Campbell to how Doggett was rated by the outside measures, she  replied in an e-mail: &ldquo;It absolutely would have been more accurate (for  me) to include the phrase &lsquo;one of the most&rsquo;&rdquo; instead of saying Doggett  was </span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">the</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"> most liberal  man in Congress.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">&ldquo;I&rsquo;m not a practiced  or polished politician and public speaking, like for many of us, is a  skill I&rsquo;m still honing,&rdquo; Campbell said. &ldquo;Before hundreds, or thousands  of eyes, I sometimes speed too quickly through what I&rsquo;d like to say. The  point I was making is that Mr. Doggett&rsquo;s ideology is considerably more  liberal than mine, and considerably more liberal than what many, many  Central Texans are telling me they want to see in their U.S.  representative.&rdquo;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">So, how does the doctor&rsquo;s convention  charge stick?</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Like melting butter.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Doggett is  liberal, but he&rsquo;s by no measure the most liberal member of Congress,  voting analyses show.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Campbell owned up after  we followed up. Her statement is False.</span></p>", "ruling_comments_date": "2010-06-17T13:41:10.876494", "ruling_date": "2010-06-20T06:00:00", "ruling_headline": "GOP nominee says Lloyd Doggett of Austin is No. 1 liberal in Congress", "ruling_headline_slug": "gop-nominee-says-lloyd-doggett-austin-no-1-liberal", "ruling_link_text": "Liberal, not most liberal", "ruling_state": null, "source_documents": null, "sources": "<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Congressional   Quarterly, </span><a href=\"http://innovation.cqpolitics.com/media/votestudy2009\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000099; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: underline;\">&ldquo;2009  Vote Studies: Presidential Support vs. Party Unity Scores,&rdquo;</span></a><a href=\"http://innovation.cqpolitics.com/media/votestudy2009/\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"> </span></a><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">(accessed June  15, 2010)</span></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://alt.coxnewsweb.com/statesman/politifact/06162010_donnacampbellemail.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000099; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: underline;\">E-mail</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">, Donna  Campbell, U.S. House nominee, June 16, 2010</span><br /> <br /> <a href=\"http://alt.coxnewsweb.com/statesman/politifact/06152010_keithpooleemails.doc\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000099; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: underline;\">E-mails  (Excerpted)</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">, Keith Poole, Philip H. Alston Jr.  Distinguished Chair, Department of Political Science, School of Public  and International Affairs, University of Georgia, June 15, 2010</span><br /> <br /> <span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">National   Journal, </span><a href=\"http://www.nationaljournal.com/njmagazine/nj_20100227_6238.php\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000099; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: underline;\">&ldquo;Key  Votes Used To Calculate The (2009) Ratings,&rdquo;</span></a><a href=\"http://www.nationaljournal.com/njmagazine/nj_20100227_6238.php\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"> </span></a><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">Feb. 27, 2010; </span><a href=\"http://www.nationaljournal.com/2009voteratings\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000099; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: underline;\">&ldquo;2009  Vote Ratings,&rdquo; </span></a><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">; </span><a href=\"http://www.nationaljournal.com/2008voteratings%20\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000099; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: underline;\">&ldquo;2008  Vote Ratings,&rdquo;</span></a><a href=\"http://www.nationaljournal.com/2008voteratings\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"> </span></a><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\">; </span><a href=\"http://www.nationaljournal.com/voteratings/house/lib.htm?o1=lib_composite&amp;o2=desc#vr%20\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000099; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; vertical-align: baseline; text-decoration: underline;\">&ldquo;2007  Vote Ratings&rdquo;</span></a><a href=\"http://www.nationaljournal.com/voteratings/house/lib.htm?o1=lib_composite&amp;o2=desc#vr\" target=\"_blank\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; font-style: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;\"> </span></a><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Times New Roman; color: #000000; background-color: transpare